RACE.RACE_TEXT: LONE STAR PARK RACE 1 5F Dirt CR: 83. Claiming Purse 16000. (PLUS UP TO $3,200 Open ATB) FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $15,000. Texas Bred Claiming Price $20,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ATRAS pressed the pace from the inside, was moving up from behind the dueling pair while three wide on the turn, then dug in gamely to kick clear of the inner rivals and was up in the final strides. BIG TICKET brushed rival at the start, then raced behind the leaders while four wide, bid on the turn then closed belatedly to be up for the place position. PHILO BEDDOE brushed foe at the start, then bid well to take command heading into the turn, dueled to keep the lead with an inner rival, continued to menace between rivals in the stretch and was out finished in the end for the place prize. SAINT PIO raced second to last position into the turn, made a mild bid heading into the stretch but came up empty. RUSH THE COLORS lead the way from the gate briefly, then pressed the pace from the inside, was moving up to challenge for the lead throughout the turn and into the early stretch, was used up and gave way in the end. BOLD N WILD was out run and no menace.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LONE STAR PARK RACE 2 5F Turf CR: 81. Claiming Purse 18500. (PLUS UP TO $3,700 Open ATB) FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000. Texas Bred Claiming Price $30,000. (If Deemed inadvisable by management to run this race over th e Turf course, it will be run on the main track at Five Furlongs.) (Rail at 20 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CLEAT sped to the lead shortly away from the gate, opened a clear advantage in the turn, repelled the bid of the runner-up in upper stretch and finished up convincingly. STRAIGHT LUCK broke alertly to press the pace from the rail, made a bold bid in upper stretch, was no match for the winner but proved a clear second best in a good effort. PITALE dueled for the early lead from between horses, backed out of the duel to track from third and failed to gain on the leaders in the lane. TEO settled along the fence to track the pacesetters through the turn, drifted into the gap in the rail down the stretch, and finished up evenly. SAINT CHARLES reserved off the leaders down the backstretch, split horses while rallying through the turn and kept on in the drive with a mild late bid. SEARING bumped at the start to be slow early to be at the back of the field and made up ground in the stretch passing tiring rivals. MIDNIGHT HUNTER tracked the pace in the clear to the turn and lacked a response when called upon. JERSEY JIM bumped at start between rivals, dropped to rear of the field, was getting out on the turn racing wide and was never a factor.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: TRES SOLES chased the pace from the inside, was gaining swiftly on the far turn to vie for the lead while three wide, then took command in the early stretch and held on grudgingly till the end. COSMIC SOUL was under a steady drive to stalk the pace from the inside down the backstretch and into the far turn, then rallied in the early stretch to surge down the final furlong to be up for the pace prize. MOR LANA SPIRIT chased the pace while two wide, was urging strongly on the far turn then closed willingly in the stretch and was best for third in the end. BRATTON lead the way into the first turn, was in a long drive down the backstretch and into the turn, then faltered in the stretch. RACE.FOOTNOTES: CHOJO raced up the rail shortly away from the gate to take the lead, battled through the turn, opened a clear advantage in upper stretch and held on to the wire in a game effort. CINNAMON FACE broke well and was taken in hand to settle off the early pace, commenced a four wide rally into the turn and finished with a rush to just miss. SUGAR MAMAS CAKERY stalked the pace from three wide through the turn, mounted a strong bid through the lane and was just out-finished for the place while gaining at the wire. OUR PASTOR pressed the pace from between rivals to midway on the turn, dropped off the leaders and finished willingly through the stretch. SKY ROCKER saved ground for the run down the backstretch along the fence, angled out for the drive and made a mild bid in the drive. LOANA reserved near the rear of the field to the turn and made a late rally passing tiring foes. HAPPY IN HEELS raced in mid-field down the backside, was set to an early drive into the turn and flattened out. BOLD EXAGGERATION broke awkwardly almost losing the rider, dropped to the back, raced wide and was never a factor. PEYTON KENNEDY flashed brief speed and was through early.
